 * 121 <= 144, 119 digits < 128 render scratch) -- only the guard priced it; lifted 10 -> 11.
 * Burnside over S_11 in exact bigint, the two INDEPENDENT routes (permutation flood over all
 * 11! = 39,916,800 permutations / cycle-type partition arithmetic) agreeing to the digit.
 * Observed 2026-07-14, pinned here:
 *
 *   n=11 all   2.554...e118 (119 digits) -- the exact iso-count of 11^121 ~ 10^126 binary
 *              operations on eleven tokens, counted without enumerating one
 *   n=11 comm  1.351...e61  (62 digits)
 *
 * The gate re-anchors to the SEALED Omega-2 n = 10 digits first (the guard edit changed no
 * sealed output), then requires route agreement AND the digit strings at n = 11; n = 12
 * refuses BY NAME (the next envelope turn: arrays 16, render 192, a 479M-permutation flood --
 * PRICED, not hidden).  EXIT 99. */
module corpus_2734_mathesis_census11

extern @abi(c-msvc-x64) fn mce_burnside(n: i64, comm: i64) -> i64 from "mathesis_census.iii"
